{
  "message": "fix(ffs-core): bound enable_writes alloc-state by device size\n\nOpenFs::load_ext4_alloc_state pre-allocated Vec::with_capacity\n(geo.group_count) without validating that group_count was physically\nplausible for the underlying byte device. A corrupted superblock\nadvertising blocks_count near u32::MAX produced ~53M groups for a\n128 KiB image; with ~56 B per GroupStats entry, the upfront\nallocation reached ~3 GiB and OOM'd the process before the first\nread_group_desc could fail.\n\nAdd a guard: reject the open with FfsError::Format if group_count\nexceeds dev.len_bytes() / block_size. Each group occupies at least\none block on disk, so any larger value is a malformed superblock\nthat read_group_desc would reject anyway \u2014 but only after the\n3 GiB allocation has been wasted.\n\nDetected by fuzz_openfs_recovery on a 32-byte input\n(blocks_count = 0x66002074, mode=Ext4Dirty + write_u32_le focused\nmutation). Promote the artifact to corpus as\nregression_oom_huge_blocks_count_alloc, plus 9 minimized libFuzzer\ndescendants from the bw_tree consolidation oracle fix and the\ndir_operations duplicate-name fix as additional regression seeds.\n\n37K-run fuzz pass clean post-fix; all enable_writes unit tests pass.",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "e4fbdd5696544f1c11a5cf4c5197743daec3bf9b",
      "filename": "crates/ffs-core/src/lib.rs",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 22,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 22,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenfs/blob/f7597e2ba8fd5a891d88f42c02f98b20999df553/crates%2Fffs-core%2Fsrc%2Flib.rs",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenfs/raw/f7597e2ba8fd5a891d88f42c02f98b20999df553/crates%2Fffs-core%2Fsrc%2Flib.rs",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Dicklesworthstone/frankenfs/contents/crates%2Fffs-core%2Fsrc%2Flib.rs?ref=f7597e2ba8fd5a891d88f42c02f98b20999df553",
      "patch": "@@ -4172,6 +4172,28 @@ impl OpenFs {\n         let geo = FsGeometry::from_superblock(sb);\n         let block_size = sb.block_size;\n         // Load group descriptors from disk.\n+        // Reject corrupted superblocks whose group_count cannot physically\n+        // fit in the underlying byte device: each group requires at least\n+        // one descriptor entry plus its own bitmap and inode-table blocks,\n+        // so an upper bound on group_count is image_blocks itself.\n+        //\n+        // A pre-fix Vec::with_capacity(geo.group_count) would happily\n+        // allocate 56 B \u00d7 u32::MAX \u2248 240 GiB and OOM the process before\n+        // the first read_group_desc could fail. Detected by\n+        // fuzz_openfs_recovery on a 32-byte input that pushed blocks_count\n+        // to ~1.7B (53M groups, ~3 GiB allocation) on a 128 KiB image.\n+        let device_blocks = if block_size == 0 {\n+            0\n+        } else {\n+            self.dev.len_bytes() / u64::from(block_size)\n+        };\n+        if u64::from(geo.group_count) > device_blocks {\n+            return Err(FfsError::Format(format!(\n+                \"ext4 superblock advertises {} groups but device only holds {} blocks; \\\n+                 refusing to allocate group state\",\n+                geo.group_count, device_blocks\n+            )));\n+        }\n         let mut groups = Vec::with_capacity(geo.group_count as usize);\n         let geom = self\n             .ext4_geometry"
    },
